<p>Both prices and products can be uploaded via excel documents, which is much easier than manually typing them in.  There are links here for pre-filled out spreadsheets for you to play with.  Be advised that the table displaces the last prices uploaded, not the prcies of the nearest date.</p>
<br>

<h3> Upload Products via excel</h3>
<form class="uploadProducts" >
	<label>
		File: <input type="file" name="sheet" id="productsSheet" type="xls|xlsx">
	</label>
	<input type="submit" value="Import!">
</form>
<br>
<h3><a href="/excel/seeded_products.xlsx">Download a sample product sheet</a><h3>

<br>
<h3> Upload Company Prices via excel</h3>
<form class="uploadCompanyPrices" >
	<label> Month:
		<% var months = ["January", "February", "March", "April", "May", "June", "July", "August", "September", "October",
		"November", "December", "Quarter 1", "Quarter 2", "Quarter 3", "Quarter 4", "Year"] %>
		<select name="month">
			<option value="0">--------------</option>
			<% for(i = 1; i <= months.length; i++){ %>
				<option value="<%= i %>"> <%= months[i - 1] %>  </option>
			<% }; %>
		</select>
	</label><br>
	<label> Year:
		<input type="text" name="year">
	</label>
	<label><br>
		File: <input type="file" name="sheet" id="companyPricesSheet" type="xls|xlsx">
	</label>
	<input type="submit" value="Import!">
</form>
<br>
<h3><a href="/excel/seeded_price_uploads.xlsx">Download a sample price sheet</a></h3>